{"article_id":"FXrIrod6gopTcVXO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" The 360 \" shows you diverse perspectives on the day ' s top stories .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Ever since the House of Representatives voted to impeach President Trump last month ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"a key point of contention has been whether the impending Senate trial would include witness testimony .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Republican Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell has said","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"he prefers a swift trial with no new witnesses .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Democrats in the Senate want to hear from administration officials at the center of Trump ' s interactions with Ukraine ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"including acting White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney and former national security adviser John Bolton .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"On Monday , Bolton said","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"he ' d be willing to testify","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"if subpoenaed by the Senate .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"All procedural rules for the trial are decided by a majority vote .","depth":4},{"id":11,"text":"With 53 Republicans in the Senate , only a handful of GOP senators would need to break party ranks","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"to force McConnell to call witnesses .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"So far , Mitt Romney is the only Senate Republican","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"to publicly call for testimony .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"On Tuesday , McConnell said","depth":4},{"id":16,"text":"he has the 51-vote majority","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"needed to start the impeachment trial","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"but would postpone a decision","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"on whether to call witnesses .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"Democrats have accused McConnell of trying to rush through a rigged trial","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"without properly investigating allegations","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that Trump abused his power","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"by withholding military aid from Ukraine .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"\" A trial","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"without all the facts","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"is a farce , \"","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer said .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"The public would be denied the opportunity","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"to fully judge the president 's actions","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"without hearing from the people closest to him ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"Democrats have argued .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Bolton ' s willingness","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"to testify","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"means Republicans have \" run out of excuses \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"for refusing to call witnesses ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"McConnell and many Republicans say","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"they ' re under no obligation to call witnesses ,","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"given that the Senate trial will almost certainly end in an acquittal","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"that allows Trump to remain in office .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"They argue","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"that Democrats had the chance","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"to pursue testimony from anyone","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"they wanted","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"when they controlled proceedings in the House ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"but chose not to pursue legal channels","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that could have compelled reluctant administration officials to appear .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"The president has reportedly advocated for a made-for-TV spectacle of a trial , with witness testimony from those","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"he sees as political enemies","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"- like Joe Biden and Adam Schiff ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"who led the House impeachment inquiry .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Trump has recently shifted his thinking on the matter ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"according to reports .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"Nancy Pelosi announced on Friday","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that she plans to send the articles of impeachment to the Senate next week .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Once the articles have been received ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"McConnell can start the trial","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"- with the question of witnesses still unanswered -","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"as soon as he likes .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Witnesses are necessary","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"to fully judge Trump ' s guilt or innocence","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"\" A standard","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"requiring proof of corrupt motive beyond a reasonable doubt","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"is unworkable","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"without witnesses .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"Testimony of witnesses","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"who spoke directly with the president","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"can raise or dispel doubts about motive","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"and should be given the chance","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"to perform that essential function. \"","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"- Evan A. Davis , The Hill","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"\" The Senate impeachment trial will be a sham","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"unless top administration officials testify. \"","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"- Editorial , New York Times","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"Witnesses would make the trial more fair for all parties","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"\" A trial with witnesses would be both fair to Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"whose lawyers should be able to cross-examine them ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"and in the national interest. \"","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"- Editorial , Los Angeles Times","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"The impeachment trial would be incomplete","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"without hearing from Bolton","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"\" Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell was dreadfully wrong from the start","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"to say","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"he might hold a trial","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"without witnesses .","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"Now , though , his excuses have run out . ... With Bolton now available to the Senate","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"without the need of a separate court fight ,","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"it would be unconscionable for McConnell not to hear his witness. \"","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"- Quin Hillyer , Washington Examiner","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"The Senate has power","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"to compel testimony","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"that the House lacks","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"\" If the Senate wishes to conduct a fair trial","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"and provide the American people with the witnesses and evidence","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"that heretofore has been hidden by the Trump administration ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"there is no need","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"to interrupt a Senate trial","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"to go to court","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"to obtain relief. \"","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"- James Robenalt , Bulwark","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":201,"left":0,"right":200,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":200,"left":114,"right":199,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":114,"left":109,"right":113,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":104,"right":108,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":102,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":103,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":108,"left":105,"right":107,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":105,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":7,"right":106,"relation":"attribu